# c1bb07eac96146efb20fc1ddc016003a
#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:147
msgid ""
"You can also create more complicated buildings by using the merge option. "
"Create your building outline, select all of the polygons (press :kbd:`SHIFT` "
"to highlight them all) and then hit :kbd:`SHIFT + J` to merge the objects."
msgstr ""

# 6f372ddf4c814e05ae95973d8bc6fef9
#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:154
msgid ""
"Furthermore, you can also change the default settings (size and tagging) on :"
"menuselection:`Data > Set building size`"
msgstr ""

# 18ffb48bcf524cf7811e3bc0c4ced1ba
#: ../../source/training/intermediate/osm/301-advanced-editing.rst:160
msgid ""
"If you are dealing with a similar size of building, you can change building "
"in certain dimensions, such as 5 x 6 meter (unit in meter). Furthermore, if "
"you mapping same infrastructure, such as townhouses in same area, you can "
"edit tags on :guilabel:`Advanced` tab that all objects are mapped into same "
"building tools."
